<p>			  Financial and Operational Data</p>
<p>				    (unaudited)</p>
<p>(1)  Minority interest includes approximately $121,000 related to</p>
<p>Bay Countrybrook L.P.</p>
<p>(2)  Extraordinary item reflects a one-time write off of</p>
<p>unamortized loan and non-use fees.</p>
<p>(3)  Funds from operations-revised definition is the</p>
<p>definition of FFO adopted in 1995 by the NAREIT Board of</p>
<p>Governors.  It represents net income plus all depreciation</p>
<p>and amortization, except depreciation for non-real estate</p>
<p>assets and amortization of recurring financing costs.</p>
<p>(4)  Funds from operations-previous definition represents</p>
<p>net income plus all depreciation and amortization.</p>
<p>(5)  Funds available for distribution represents net income</p>
<p>plus all depreciation and amortization less capital</p>
<p>expenditures and loan principal payments.</p>
<p>(6)  Fixed debt includes floating rate debt swapped to a</p>
<p>long-term fixed rate.</p>
<p>(7)  Construction debt includes amounts drawn from the line</p>
<p>of credit for development and construction purposes.</p>
<p>(8)  Book capitalization excludes accumulated depreciation. (9)  Debt service coverage represents EBITDA divided by the</p>
<p>sum of interest expense and loan principal amortization</p>
<p>payments (excluding balloon payments).</p>
<p>(10) Debt service coverage represents EBITDA divided by the</p>
<p>sum of interest expense, capitalized interest and loan</p>
<p>principal amortization payments (excluding balloon</p>
<p>payments).</p>
<p>(11) The company, as a matter of policy, expenses any apartment-</p>
<p>related expenditures less than $5,000.  These normally include</p>
<p>any expenditure related to the interior of an apartment.</p>
<p>The company typically capitalizes expenditures such as those</p>
<p>for new security gate systems, leasing pavilion reconstruction</p>
<p>and redecorating, roofing repair and replacement, exterior</p>
<p>siding repair and repainting and parking area resurfacing.</p>
<p>Capitalized expenditures as described here exclude major</p>
<p>reconstruction costs incurred in conjunction with the</p>
<p>acquisition and repositioning of newly purchased apartment</p>
<p>communities.  Such costs are added to the purchase price of</p>
<p>those communities.  Capitalized expenditures also exclude the</p>
<p>cost of cashflow enhancing improvements such as those</p>
<p>expended for construction of new garages or installation of</p>
<p>water conservation devices which almost immediately and</p>
<p>permanently either earn additional revenue or reduce expenses. (12) Physical occupancy is that at the end of the period</p>
<p>indicated.</p>
<p>(13) Same store communities are those communities owned</p>
<p>prior to the IPO plus four post-IPO acquisitions.  They</p>
<p>comprise a total of 3,330 apartment homes.  These apartment</p>
<p>communities include all those which were owned for all of</p>
<p>1995 and the first three quarters of 1996 and to which the</p>
<p>company made no major renovations after January 1, 1995.</p>
